Residents in Gambella city, capital of one of Ethiopia’s eleven regions, Gambella, said offices and business were closed due to the intensified fighting. Some of the fighting is around the regional president’s office, according to the residents, The region’s President Umod Ubang has told the BBC that he has no information to share. Fighting has also been reported in towns in the neighbouring regions of Oromia. A Spokesperson for the armed group Oromo Liberation Army (OLA), Odda Tarbii, has tweeted that "a joint operation" between his group and the Gambella Liberation Front was under way in Gambella. --BBC--